It's believed the 58-year old man had an argument with his 24-year old son yesterday morning. JOHANNESBURG - A man is facing a charge of murder after fatally stabbing his son in Nqamakwe in the Eastern Cape. It's believed the 58-year old man had an argument with his 24-year old son yesterday morning. The police's Jackson Manatha says the father will appear in court tomorrow on a charge of murder. “The son followed his father and he started to shout at him, the suspect withdrew his knife and fatally stabbed his body.”